Film & Documentary

Death in Bali: A Joyful Celebration

Death, in many places, is celebrated as a tragic experience that makes us feel melancholic. However, in Bali, Indonesia, known as Ngaben, death is celebrated through a joyful party, especially for a deceased King. Almost no cries, a lot of laugh.

The Boy & The Ogoh-Ogoh

In traditional tales of Balinese culture, Ogoh-Ogoh emerges as shadowy reflection of our inner fears and other negative emotion. Through the lens of a child's innocence, this encounter weaves a delicate combination between documentary and reality. Such artistry unveils the essence of Balinese culture with a subtle grace, inviting exploration with a poetic whisper.
